---
// Commodities section component
---

<section id="commodities" class="section section-alt" aria-label="Our commodities">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">What We Trade</p>
      <h2 class="display-2 silver">Three commodities. One reliable partner.</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="card-grid">
      <article class="commodity-card reveal">
        <div class="card-media">
          <img src="/assets/commodity-coal.jpg" alt="Coal commodity" loading="lazy" width="800" height="800" />
          <span class="card-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M8.5 14.5A2.5 2.5 0 0 0 11 12c0-1.38-.5-2-1-3-1.072-2.143-.224-4.054 2-6 .5 2.5 2 4.9 4 6.5 2 1.6 3 3.5 3 5.5a7 7 0 1 1-14 0c0-1.153.433-2.294 1-3a2.5 2.5 0 0 0 2.5 2.5z"/></svg></span>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <h3>Coal</h3>
          <p>Thermal and metallurgical coal sourced from reputable South African producers. We handle both domestic supply — for industrial users, cement and power generation — and export-destined cargoes bound for seaborne markets via established coastal and overland routes.</p>
          <p>Every cargo is supported by independent sampling, SANAS-referenced weighbridge tickets and chain-of-custody documentation, so buyers receive exactly what was contracted, on spec.</p>
          <a href="#contact" class="link-arrow">Request a quote <span>→</span></a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="commodity-card reveal delay-1">
        <div class="card-media">
          <img src="/assets/commodity-chrome.jpg" alt="Chrome commodity" loading="lazy" width="800" height="800" />
          <span class="card-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="m8 3 4 8 5-5 5 15H2L8 3z"/></svg></span>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <h3>Chrome</h3>
          <p>Chrome ore, lumpy and concentrate sourced from the Bushveld Complex — the world's largest chrome resource. We supply local smelters and export buyers, with careful attention to grade consistency, Cr:Fe ratio and moisture management from pit to port.</p>
          <p>Cargoes move under full export documentation, independent inspection and weighbridge reconciliation, giving both producer and buyer a clear audit trail on every parcel.</p>
          <a href="#contact" class="link-arrow">Request a quote <span>→</span></a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="commodity-card reveal delay-2">
        <div class="card-media">
          <img src="/assets/commodity-feed.jpg" alt="Animal feed commodity" loading="lazy" width="800" height="800" />
          <span class="card-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M2 22 16 8M3.47 12.53 5 11l1.53 1.53a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 0 4.94L5 19l-1.53-1.53a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 0-4.94zM7.47 8.53 9 7l1.53 1.53a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 0 4.94L9 15l-1.53-1.53a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 0-4.94zM11.47 4.53 13 3l1.53 1.53a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 0 4.94L13 11l-1.53-1.53a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 0-4.94z"/></svg></span>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <h3>Animal Feed</h3>
          <p>Bulk animal feed and raw ingredients — including maize, soybean meal, sunflower oilcake and finished rations — for commercial poultry, dairy, beef-feedlot and pig operations across South Africa and neighbouring SADC markets.</p>
          <p>All product is sourced from Act 36 registered manufacturers and moved in equipment matched to the material — tippers, side-tippers or pneumatic blowers — with moisture and biosecurity controls maintained through to on-farm silo discharge.</p>
          <a href="#contact" class="link-arrow">Request a quote <span>→</span></a>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
